{"title_page": "1953\u201354 DDR-Oberliga", "text_new": "{{Other|1953\u201354 Oberliga (disambiguation)}}\n{{infobox football league season\n| competition        = [[DDR-Oberliga]]\n| logo               = \n| image              = \n| season             = 1953\u201354\n| winners            = [[FC Rot-Weiss Erfurt|BSG Turbine Erfurt]]\n| promoted           = \n| relegated          = {{ubl|[[Lok Stendal|BSG Lokomotive Stendal]]|[[SV Dessau 05|Motor Dessau]]|[[BSG Stahl Thale]]}}\n| continentalcup1    = \n| continentalcup1 qualifiers = \n| matches            = 210\n| total goals        = 676\n| league topscorer   = [[Heinz Satrapa]] (21)<ref name=\"Goal\" />\n| attendance         = 2,941,000<ref name=\"Fuwo\" >''fuwo'', page: 23</ref>\n| average attendance = 14,005<ref name=\"Fuwo\" />\n| prevseason = [[1952\u201353 DDR-Oberliga|1952\u201353]]\n| nextseason = [[1954\u201355 DDR-Oberliga|1954\u201355]]\n}}\nThe '''1953\u201354 DDR-Oberliga''' was the fifth season of the [[DDR-Oberliga]], the first tier of [[East German football league system|league football]] in [[East Germany]]. \n\nThe league was contested by fifteen teams, two less than in the previous season, and [[FC Rot-Weiss Erfurt|BSG Turbine Erfurt]] won the championship. It was the first of two championships for the club, winning it the following season as well.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesd/ddrchamp.html |title= East Germany - List of Champions |date= |website= rsssf.com |publisher= |access-date= 19 January 2016|language=|trans-title=}}</ref><ref name=\"Meister\" >{{cite web |url=https://www.dfb.de/historie/ddr-fussball/meister/ |title= DDR-Meister |date= |website=dfb.de |publisher=[[German Football Association]] |access-date= 19 January 2016|language=German|trans-title= East German champions}}</ref>\n\n[[Heinz Satrapa]] of [[BSG Wismut Aue]] was the league's top scorer with 21 goals.<ref name=\"Goal\" >{{cite web |url=http://www.weltfussball.de/torschuetzenkoenige/gdr-oberliga/ |title= DDDR \u00bb Oberliga \u00bb Torsch\u00fctzenk\u00f6nige  |date= |website= Weltfussball.de |publisher= |access-date= 19 January 2016|language=German|trans-title=DDR-Oberliga top scorers }}</ref>\n\nThe 1953\u201354 season saw the best-ever average support for the Oberliga with 14,005 spectators per game.<ref name=\"Fuwo\" />\n\n==Table==\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\nThe 1953\u201354 season saw two newly promoted clubs, [[Fortschritt Meerane]] and [[Lokomotive Leipzig|Einheit Ost Leipzig]]. The [[FDGB-Pokal]] was won by second division [[DDR-Liga]] club [[Vorw\u00e4rts Berlin]].<ref name=\"Ddr\" >{{cite web |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesd/ddrhist.html |title= East Germany 1946-1990 |date= |website= rsssf.com |publisher= |access-date= 19 January 2016|language=|trans-title=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.weltfussball.de/spielplan/gdr-oberliga-1953-1954-spieltag/28/ |title= DDR \u00bb Oberliga 1953/1954 |date= |website= Weltfussball.de |publisher= |access-date= 19 January 2016|language=German|trans-title=DDR-Oberliga 1953\u201354}}</ref>\t\t\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=Q\n|sortable_table=y\n|winpoints=2\n|use_goal_ratio=y\n\n|team1=ERF|name_ERF=[[FC Rot-Weiss Erfurt|BSG Turbine Erfurt]]\n|team2=CHM|name_CHM=[[FC Sachsen Leipzig|BSG Chemie Leipzig]]\n|team3=DYN|name_DYN=[[Dynamo Dresden]]\n|team4=WIS|name_WIS=[[FC Erzgebirge Aue|BSG Wismut Aue]]\n|team5=BAB|name_BAB=[[Fortuna Babelsberg|BSG Rotation Babelsberg]]\n|team6=ABO|name_ABO=[[BSG Aktivist Brieske-Ost]]\n|team7=ROT|name_ROT=[[BSG Rotation Dresden]]\n|team8=HAL|name_HAL=[[Hallescher FC|BSG Turbine Halle]]\n|team9=EMP|name_EMP=[[Empor Lauter]]\n|team10=MEE|name_MEE=[[Fortschritt Meerane]]\n|team11=ZWI|name_ZWI=[[FSV Zwickau|BSG Motor Zwickau]]\n|team12=EIN|name_EIN=[[Lokomotive Leipzig|Einheit Ost Leipzig]]\n|team13=STN|name_STN=[[Lok Stendal|BSG Lokomotive Stendal]]\n|team14=DES|name_DES=[[SV Dessau 05|Motor Dessau]]\n|team15=THA|name_THA=[[BSG Stahl Thale]]\n|win_ERF=17|draw_ERF=5|loss_ERF=6|gf_ERF=58|ga_ERF=36\n|win_CHM=15|draw_CHM=5|loss_CHM=8|gf_CHM=51|ga_CHM=37\n|win_DYN=15|draw_DYN=4|loss_DYN=9|gf_DYN=54|ga_DYN=44\n|win_WIS=15|draw_WIS=3|loss_WIS=10|gf_WIS=59|ga_WIS=42\n|win_BAB=12|draw_BAB=8|loss_BAB=8|gf_BAB=58|ga_BAB=43\n|win_ABO=11|draw_ABO=8|loss_ABO=9|gf_ABO=48|ga_ABO=43\n|win_ROT=9|draw_ROT=10|loss_ROT=9|gf_ROT=46|ga_ROT=39\n|win_HAL=11|draw_HAL=6|loss_HAL=11|gf_HAL=30|ga_HAL=30\n|win_EMP=8|draw_EMP=11|loss_EMP=9|gf_EMP=40|ga_EMP=38\n|win_MEE=8|draw_MEE=9|loss_MEE=11|gf_MEE=46|ga_MEE=46\n|win_ZWI=10|draw_ZWI=5|loss_ZWI=13|gf_ZWI=39|ga_ZWI=56\n|win_EIN=9|draw_EIN=5|loss_EIN=14|gf_EIN=43|ga_EIN=57\n|win_STN=6|draw_STN=11|loss_STN=11|gf_STN=38|ga_STN=51\n|win_DES=7|draw_DES=9|loss_DES=12|gf_DES=38|ga_DES=55\n|win_THA=4|draw_THA=7|loss_THA=17|gf_THA=28|ga_THA=59\n\n|col_C=green1|text_C=League champion\n|result1=C\n<!--\n|col_FPW=lavender|text_FPW=[[FDGB-Pokal]] winner\n-->\n|col_R=red1|text_R=Relegated\n|result13=R|result14=R|result15=R\n|update=complete|source=\n}}\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n===Sources===\n* {{cite magazine |last= |first= |date=1991 |title= Das war unser Fu\u00dfball im Osten|trans-title= This was our football in the East|language=German |magazine= Fu\u00dfball-Woche (fuwo)|location=Berlin |publisher=[[Axel Springer SE|Axel-Springer-Verlag]]}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.f-archiv.de/ Das Deutsche Fussball Archiv] {{in lang|de}} Historic German league tables\n\n{{DDR-Oberliga seasons}}\n{{1953\u201354 in European football (UEFA)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ddr-Oberliga 1953-54}}\n[[Category:DDR-Oberliga seasons|1953-54]]\n[[Category:1953\u201354 in German football leagues|Ober]]\n[[Category:1953\u201354 in East German football]]\n", "text_old": "{{Other|1953\u201354 Oberliga (disambiguation)}}\n{{infobox football league season\n| competition                = [[DDR-Oberliga]]\n| logo                       = \n| image                      =\n| pixels                     = \n| season                     = 1953\u201354\n| winners                    = [[FC Rot-Weiss Erfurt|BSG Turbine Erfurt]]\n| promoted                   = \n| relegated                  = [[Lok Stendal|BSG Lokomotive Stendal]]{{-}}[[SV Dessau 05|Motor Dessau]]{{-}}[[BSG Stahl Thale]]\n| continentalcup1            = \n| continentalcup1 qualifiers = \n| matches                       = 210\n| total goals                     = 676\n| league topscorer           = [[Heinz Satrapa]] (21)<ref name=\"Goal\" />\n| attendance                    = 2,941,000<ref name=\"Fuwo\" >''fuwo'', page: 23</ref>\n| average attendance      = 14,005<ref name=\"Fuwo\" />\n| prevseason                 = [[1952\u201353 DDR-Oberliga|1952\u201353]]\n| nextseason                 = [[1954\u201355 DDR-Oberliga|1954\u201355]]\n}}\nThe '''1953\u201354 DDR-Oberliga''' was the fifth season of the [[DDR-Oberliga]], the first tier of [[East German football league system|league football]] in [[East Germany]]. \n\nThe league was contested by fifteen teams, two less than in the previous season, and [[FC Rot-Weiss Erfurt|BSG Turbine Erfurt]] won the championship. It was the first of two championships for the club, winning it the following season as well.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesd/ddrchamp.html |title= East Germany - List of Champions |date= |website= rsssf.com |publisher= |access-date= 19 January 2016|language=|trans-title=}}</ref><ref name=\"Meister\" >{{cite web |url=https://www.dfb.de/historie/ddr-fussball/meister/ |title= DDR-Meister |date= |website=dfb.de |publisher=[[German Football Association]] |access-date= 19 January 2016|language=German|trans-title= East German champions}}</ref>\n\n[[Heinz Satrapa]] of [[BSG Wismut Aue]] was the league's top scorer with 21 goals.<ref name=\"Goal\" >{{cite web |url=http://www.weltfussball.de/torschuetzenkoenige/gdr-oberliga/ |title= DDDR \u00bb Oberliga \u00bb Torsch\u00fctzenk\u00f6nige  |date= |website= Weltfussball.de |publisher= |access-date= 19 January 2016|language=German|trans-title=DDR-Oberliga top scorers }}</ref>\n\nThe 1953\u201354 season saw the best-ever average support for the Oberliga with 14,005 spectators per game.<ref name=\"Fuwo\" />\n\n==Table==\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\nThe 1953\u201354 season saw two newly promoted clubs, [[Fortschritt Meerane]] and [[Lokomotive Leipzig|Einheit Ost Leipzig]]. The [[FDGB-Pokal]] was won by second division [[DDR-Liga]] club [[Vorw\u00e4rts Berlin]].<ref name=\"Ddr\" >{{cite web |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesd/ddrhist.html |title= East Germany 1946-1990 |date= |website= rsssf.com |publisher= |access-date= 19 January 2016|language=|trans-title=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.weltfussball.de/spielplan/gdr-oberliga-1953-1954-spieltag/28/ |title= DDR \u00bb Oberliga 1953/1954 |date= |website= Weltfussball.de |publisher= |access-date= 19 January 2016|language=German|trans-title=DDR-Oberliga 1953\u201354}}</ref>\t\t\n{{fb cl header|sort=y|winpoints=2|gavg=y|noqr=y}}\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#ccffcc\"\n||1||[[FC Rot-Weiss Erfurt|BSG Turbine Erfurt]]||28||17||5||6||58||36||1,61||39\n|-\n||2||[[FC Sachsen Leipzig|BSG Chemie Leipzig]]||28||15||5||8||51||37||1,38||35\n|-\n||3||[[Dynamo Dresden]]||28||15||4||9||54||44||1,23||34\n|-\n||4||[[FC Erzgebirge Aue|BSG Wismut Aue]]||28||15||3||10||59||42||1,41||33\n|-\n||5||[[Fortuna Babelsberg|BSG Rotation Babelsberg]]||28||12||8||8||58||43||1,35||32\n|-\n||6||[[BSG Aktivist Brieske-Ost]]||28||11||8||9||48||43||1,12||30\n|-\n||7||[[BSG Rotation Dresden]]||28||9||10||9||46||39||1,18||28\n|-\n||8||[[Hallescher FC|BSG Turbine Halle]]||28||11||6||11||30||30||1,00||28\n|-\n||9||[[Empor Lauter]]||28||8||11||9||40||38||1,05||27\n|-\n||10||[[Fortschritt Meerane]]||28||8||9||11||46||46||1,00||25\n|-\n||11||[[FSV Zwickau|BSG Motor Zwickau]]||28||10||5||13||39||56||0,70||25\n|-\n||12||[[Lokomotive Leipzig|Einheit Ost Leipzig]]||28||9||5||14||43||57||0,754||23\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#ffcccc\"\n||13||[[Lok Stendal|BSG Lokomotive Stendal]]||28||6||11||11||38||51||0,745||